{"lemma":"عَقِيبَةٍ","slug":"عَقِيبَةٍ","root":"ع.ق.ب","root_slug":"ع-ق-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29848","n29850"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29848","headword_ar":"عَقِيبٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything that is a sequent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of, or to, another thing; ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in an absolute sense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as when you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alaAmu EaqiybN lilt~a$ah~udi","text_ar":"السَّلَامُ عَقِيبٌ لِلتَّشَهُّدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The salutation is a sequent to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t$h~d","text_ar":"تشهّد"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.)], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEid~apu EaqiybN lilT~alaAqi","text_ar":"العِدَّةُ عَقِيبٌ لِلطَّلَاقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eid~ap","text_ar":"عِدَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is a sequent to divorcement"},{"kind":"text","text":"], i. e., one follows the other; (Msb;) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by alternation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as when one says of the night and the day,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u waAHidK minohumaA Eaqiybu","text_ar":"كُلُّ وَاحِدٍ مِنْهُمَا عَقِيبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibihi","text_ar":"صَاحِبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Each of them is the alternating sequent of its correlative"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Az, Msb, TA:) you say of the night and the day,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA EaqiybaAni","text_ar":"هُمَا عَقِيبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are two alternating sequents"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqiybuka","text_ar":"عَقِيبُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who does a deed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"work, with thee by turn, he doing it one time and thou another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaAqibN","text_ar":"مُعَاقِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, (S, Msb,) as also [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEoqibN","text_ar":"مُعْقِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEotaqibN","text_ar":"مُعْتَقِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaq~ibN","text_ar":"مُعَقِّبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) As for the saying of the lawyers,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafoEalu *`lika Eaqiyba","text_ar":"يَفْعَلُ ذٰلِكَ عَقِيبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaApi","text_ar":"الصَّلَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He does that after the prayer"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and the like thereof, there is no reason to be given but a suppression; the meaning being,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqotK Eaqiyb waqoti AlS~alaApi","text_ar":"وَقْتٍ عَقِيب وَقْتِ الصَّلَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a time following that of prayer"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqyb","text_ar":"عقيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"being an epithet qualifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wqt","text_ar":"وقت"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and Er-Rázee says, in the Mukhtár es- Siháh, that he had found no authority in the T nor in the S for the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a Eaqiybahu","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ عَقِيبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came after him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqibN","text_ar":"عَقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence. [And compare"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqibN","text_ar":"عَاقِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","TA","Az"]},{"entry_id":"n29850","headword_ar":"عُقَيِّبٌ","root":"Eqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", with teshdeed of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euq~ayobN","text_ar":"عُقَّيْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qub~ayoTN","text_ar":"قُبَّيْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) [If the name be correctly as in the O, the bird meant is probably"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an eaglet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small species of eagle."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["O","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}